DEFINITIONS
-----------
"Theme" refers to the Jekyll/GitHub Pages template source code, design,
stylesheets, layouts, includes, and associated files in this repository.

"Personal License" means a single license purchased for use on one (1)
personal, non-commercial project.

"Commercial License" means a single license purchased for use on one (1)
client or commercial project that generates revenue or is used for business
purposes.

FREE USE WITH ATTRIBUTION
--------------------------
You MAY use this Theme on any personal, non-commercial project for free,
provided that:

  1. The footer attribution block is kept intact and visible on every page:
       "Theme by csswitch · Remove attribution →"
  2. You do not modify or hide the attribution HTML comment or the
     .csswitch-attr element.
  3. You do not use the Theme for any commercial or revenue-generating purpose.

PAID LICENSE — REMOVES ATTRIBUTION
------------------------------------
By purchasing a license at https://csswitch.gumroad.com you receive:

  - Permission to remove the footer attribution block.
  - Permission to use the Theme on ONE (1) live project (personal or
    commercial).
  - Access to future updates of this Theme.
  - Private source repository access (collaborator invite).

A separate license must be purchased for each additional project or client.

WHAT REQUIRES A PAID LICENSE
-----------------------------
You MUST purchase a license if you:
  - Want to remove the footer attribution.
  - Use the Theme on a commercial or revenue-generating site.
  - Use the Theme in a project for a client, employer, or third party.

YOU MAY NOT (with or without a paid license):
  - Redistribute, resell, lease, sub-license, or offer the Theme
    to any third party as a standalone product or template.
  - Include the Theme in a "theme bundle" or collection for resale.
  - Transfer your license to another person or organisation.

